casebody.data:
The State of Ohio, Appellee, v. Williams, Appellant.

[Cite as State v. Williams, 144 Ohio St.3d 247, 2015-Ohio-4537.]

(No. 2014-1884 Submitted October 14, 2015 Decided November 4, 2015.) Timothy J. McGinty, Cuyahoga County Prosecuting Attorney, and Mary H. McGrath and Frank R. Zeleznikar, Assistant Prosecuting Attorneys, for appellee. Robey & Robey and Gregory S. Robey, for appellant.

{¶ 1} The cause is dismissed, sua sponte, as having been improvidently accepted.

O’Connor, C.J., and Pfeifer, O’Donnell, Lanzinger, French, and O’Neill, JJ., concur. Kennedy, J., dissents.
